title: For Sale:  Stop Senate Bill 5737
postcontent:
This is a bill to ban what our representatives in Olympia consider "assault weapons". Originally, the wording  of Senate Bill 5737 included an annual inspection at your home: 

“In order to continue to possess an assault weapon that was legally possessed on the effective date of this section, the person possessing shall ... safely and securely store the assault weapon. The sheriff of the county may, no more than once per year, conduct an inspection to ensure compliance with this subsection.”

http://www.thehighroad.org/showthread.php?t=703933

Meaning the police would have the right to come in to your home an inspect your assault rifle to make sure you were complying with their law.

However, it seems the offending paragraph has been removed and the bill now seeks to completely outlaw simultaneous possession of semiautomatic rifle (even a pump action rifle!), pistols and shotguns "capable of accepting a detachable magazine" AND "any magazine capable of use with that firearm that contains more than ten rounds of ammunition" at the same time.

Read paragraph (2) and decide for yourself:

"NEW SECTION. Sec. 2. A new section is added to chapter 9.41 RCW
 to read as follows:

(1) No person in this state shall manufacture, possess, purchase,
 sell, or otherwise transfer any assault weapon, or any assault weapon
conversion kit, except as authorized by subsection (3) of this section.
Any assault weapon or assault weapon conversion kit the manufacture,
possession, purchase, sale, or other transfer of which is prohibited
under this section is a public nuisance.
(2) No person in this state shall possess or have under his or her
control at one time both of the following:
(a) A semiautomatic or pump-action rifle, semiautomatic pistol, or
shotgun capable of accepting a detachable magazine; and
 (b) Any magazine capable of use with that firearm that contains
more than ten rounds of ammunition.
(3) Subsection (1) of this section shall not apply to any of the
following:
(a) The possession of an unloaded assault weapon for the purpose of
permanently relinquishing it to a law enforcement agency in this state. (SB 5737 p. 6)

Apparently, this combination of a semiautomatic (or pump action) firearm (rifle, pistol or shotgun) and a magazine of more than 10 rounds constitutes an "assault rifle", and is therefore bad.

Also, while the bill says it is OK to carry what they apparently consider "assault weapons" to and from a "licensed, lawfully operated shooting range" or target shooting event, it makes no mention of carrying and using such rifles and pistols during a hunting trip. By default, that seems to be illegal.

This bill was sponsored by Ed Murray, Jeanne Kohl-Welles and Adam Kline:

http://www.leg.wa.gov/senate/senators/pages/Murray.aspx

http://www.leg.wa.gov/senate/senators/pages/Kohl-Welles.aspx

http://www.leg.wa.gov/senate/senators/pages/Kline.aspx

Please contact your representative and voice your strong disapproval to SB 5737

http://apps.leg.wa.gov/billinfo/summary.aspx?bill=5737&year=2013

Here is the bill itself. Please read it and understand what they are trying to take away!

http://apps.leg.wa.gov/documents/billdocs/2013-14/Pdf/Bills/Senate%20Bills/5737.pdf

Here is a list of all Washington State Legislators email addresses:

https://dlr.leg.wa.gov/MemberEmail/Default.aspx

Please contact them and voice your support of the 2nd Amendment. Remember, it is your pump-action assault rifle they are trying to ban.

Bill Carson

title: For Sale:  PRE-BAN DATE STAMPED 30 ROUND AR MAGAZINES.
location: New York, New York, United States
postcontent:
10 30 round Center Industries date stamped pre-ban AR-15 magazines. These mags were manufactured in various months of 1991 and bear the manufacturer date stamps to prove it. Many magazines being sold as pre-ban are not date stamped and cannot easily be proven to be pre-ban. I love the guy selling "pre-ban" P-Mags that didn't exist prior to the ban. I have numerous other magazines that I know are pre-ban because I bought them before 1994. Why am I not offering them for sale? They are not date stamped and the DA in your local NY jurisdiction is not going to take my word for it, that's why. Don't prove your mags are pre-ban (or wind up proving they aren't) with a $50,000 legal bill to beat a class D felony for possessing illegal "Large capacity ammunition feeding devices".

New York state law:

 TITLE P--OFFENSES AGAINST PUBLIC SAFETY
ARTICLE 265 --FIREARMS AND OTHER DANGEROUS WEAPONS 23

provides the following definition:

"23. Large capacity ammunition feeding device" means a magazine, belt, drum, feed strip, or similar device, manufactured after September thirteenth, nineteen hundred ninety-four, that has a capacity of, or that can be readily restored or converted to accept, more than ten rounds of ammunition; provided, however, that such term does not include an attached tubular device designed to accept, and capable of operating only with, .22 caliber rimfire ammunition."Section 265.02 Criminal possession of a weapon in the third degree

Section 265.02 of the same chapter states:

"
 A person is guilty of criminal possession of a weapon in the third degree when:

(1) Such person commits the crime of criminal possession of a weapon in the fourth degree as defined in subdivision one, two, three or five of section 265.01, and has been previously convicted of any crime; or

(2) Such person possesses any explosive or incendiary bomb, bombshell, firearm silencer, machine-gun or any other firearm or weapon simulating a machine-gun and which is adaptable for such use; or

(3) Such person knowingly possesses a machine-gun, firearm, rifle or shotgun which has been defaced for the purpose of concealment or prevention of the detection of a crime or misrepresenting the identity of such machine-gun, firearm, rifle or shotgun; or

(4) Such person possesses any loaded firearm. Such possession shall not, except as provided in subdivision one or seven, constitute a violation of this section if such possession takes place in such person's home or place of business; or

(5) (i) Such person possesses three or more firearms; or (ii) such person possesses a firearm and has been previously convicted of a felony or a class A misdemeanor defined in this chapter within the five years immediately preceding the commission of the offense and such possession did not take place in the person's home or place of business; or

(6) Such person knowingly possesses any disguised gun; or

(7) Such person possesses an assault weapon; or

(8) Such person possesses a large capacity ammunition feeding device.

Criminal possession of a weapon in the third degree is a class D felony.

"

Note the fact that magazines manufactured before 9/13/1994 are not "Large capacity ammunition feeding devices" under the current law, and yes, that's right, a magazine made after 9/13/1994 is a "weapon" and possession is a felony. Don't blame me I'm not the drooling idiot that comes up with this stuff. Look to your legislature for that and we can all look to congress.

Finish on 9 of them is factory grey and shows the sort of wear normal for a 20+ year old magazine. One has been refinished with a black paint. I don't know what, I bought it that way and it does not effect function.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Magnum Research .40 baby desert eagle (P99 replica)
postcontent: It's made to look very similar to the Walther P99. It has everything the P99 has, in fact the lower polymer portion of the gun IS the lower used on the P99. It's shipped from walther to magnum research where they create a nice heavy stainless steel slide and barrel. Still has the decock mechanism on top, the orange dot hammer in the back, super comfortable grip, and the double action trigger as the P99. The only difference is the slide is no longer polymer but stainless steel.
